name: UConn basketball
summary:
**Summary:**

The UConn men's basketball team's impressive 17-game winning streak came to an end at the Maui Invitational after a loss to Memphis. The No. 2 UConn women's team also played in the event, defeating Oregon State. Both teams are ranked in the top 25 nationally, and fans can now purchase bobbleheads to commemorate their success. Coach Geno Auriemma celebrated a historic NCAA wins record with legendary UConn players and received a goat as a gift. A large reunion is expected for the women's basketball team as they celebrate Auriemma's milestone. The men's team hopes to replicate the success of former coach Jim Calhoun's Huskies at the Maui Invitational.

name: Jack Smith
summary: Special Counsel Jack Smith has dismissed several cases against former President Donald Trump, including election subversion and classified documents investigations. Smith's decision to drop the cases was based on a Justice Department policy against prosecuting former presidents for the same offenses that led to their impeachment. As a result, a judge has approved the dismissal of Trump's 2020 election interference case, which centered on his efforts to overturn the election results. Smith's actions have effectively ended the federal criminal cases against Trump for the aforementioned charges.
